TI  - Performance of Hardwickia binataRoxb. in intensive silvo-pastoral systems in Thardesert.
T2  - Current Agriculture
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The characteristics of Hardwickia binatawhich was first introduced in the Thar desert region of Rajasthan, India are described. The adaptability of this species to arid environment, its potential for top feed production and its compatibility with other species in silvopastoral systems are discussed. The present status of adoption and the future value of species in Thar Desert are explored. It has been proven that H. binatais one of the best candidate woody components for intensive silvopastoral systems in the Thar Desert.
