TI  - Special Issue: Livelihood resilience to climate change in the Mekong River basin.
T2  - Journal of Agribusiness in Developing and Emerging Economies
M3  - Journal issue
AB  - This special issue consists of four full studies regarding livelihood adaptations in response to climate change. The first paper provides an understanding of rural household livelihoods in the Mekong Delta how they can cope with climate stressors at the ground level. The second paper examines the determinants of adaptation strategies among Vietnamese Mekong River Delta rice farmers and assesses the impacts of such practices on rice yield. Findings revealed that farmers receiving early disaster warnings are more likely to adopt adaptation measures to climate change. The third article investigates the adoption of the alternate wetting and drying (AWD) technique providing an economic evaluation and identifying the determinants of AWD adoption in rice production in the Mekong Delta in Vietnam. Lastly, the fourth paper explores the input- and output-specific technical inefficiency of Vietnamese prawn-rice rotational crops (PRRC) and identifies the impacts of the socio-economic characteristics of farmers and their farms on these technical inefficiencies.
