TI  - Effects of land use change on environment in agro-pastoral ecotone based on ecosystem services value: a case study in Taipusi, Inner Mongolia.
T2  - Acta Agrestia Sinica
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Based on 3S technology and field investigation methods, the land use change of Taipusi from 1986 to 2009 was studied. The effect of land use change on ecological environment was analyzed by calculating the change of ecosystem service value as a result of land use change. Results showed that the area of forest land and construction land increased, whereas the area of farmland, grassland and water decreased from 1986 to 2009. Land use change led to the change of ecological environment of tested area and influenced the ecosystem service value to some degree. The total ecosystem service value of Taipusi had an upward trend during 1986 to 2009. The ecological service value of forest had the fastest growth and the most contribution to total ecosystem service value compared with others. Gas regulation, climate regulation, soil formation and conservation, biodiversity conservation, raw materials and entertainment function value continued to increase due to the policy implementation of returning cultivated land to forest (grass). The vegetation conditions of tested area had been improved since 2000. But the land degradation and drought as well as other major ecological problems had not been fundamentally solved. Ecosystem service functions were not completely improved and recovered. Therefore, the reasonable configuration of land resource should comprehensively consider the various factors and practical situations of the study area.
