TI  - Satellite imagery+crop insurance=smallholder farmers' gain.
T2  - Geospatial World
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This article reports on a pilot Index-Based Flood Insurance (IBFI) scheme launched by the International Water Management Institute (IWMI) in Bihar, India, to help smallholders withstand climate shocks. The initiative is part of the efforts by IWMI to use the latest remote sensing data, Geographical Information System (GIS) technology and computer modelling to benefit poor and marginalized farmers. The approach called as AgRISE (Agricultural Remote sensing Insurance for Security and Equity) seeks to provide all farmers, no matter how small, with the security that insurance can provide.
