TI  - Small-scale aquaculture of wild fish in Myanmar: a preliminary report from the Bago Region.
T2  - Aquaculture Asia Magazine
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Results are presented from a survey of small-scale aquaculture of wild fish in the Bago Region of Myanmar. This aquaculture system is similar to rice field fisheries practices throughout floodplain areas in Asia. What makes this system different is that the fish are not just trapped and then harvested but they are fed and broodstock is selected for the next year's production. Information is presented in this paper on: the number and size of ponds; the aquaculture practices followed, including in feeding, harvesting, and broodstock selection; the species, sizes and yields of harvested fish; the markets for the fish; and the economic returns of wild fish aquaculture.
