AB  - This paper presents the results of field studies conducted in India to evaluate the agronomic characteristics, adaptability, diseases resistance and heat tolerance of HD 3298, a biofortified, climate-resilient, high-yielding wheat cultivar for very late sown conditions of north-western plains of India, developed from the two-way cross consisting of CL1449/PBW343 as the female parent and CL882/HD2009 as the male parent. Information on the release notification and seed production of this new wheat cultivar in New Delhi, India, is also presented.
