TI  - Fighting drought and aluminum toxicity: phenotypic screening and participatory evaluation with women and small-scale farmers of regional released bean lines (Phasolus vulgaris) for abiotic stress of drought and heat tolerance. Screening of regional released bean lines (Phasolus vulgaris) for abiotic stress of drought tolerance for the Shire Valley, Malawi.
T2  - Annual Report - Soil and Agricultural Engineering Commodity Group, 2007/08. Presented during the DARS Annual Planning meeting held at Andrews Holiday Resort, Mangochi, 14-19th September, 2008
M3  - Book chapter
AB  - A bean Nursery consisting of 51 drought lines (Ex-Columbia); 26 New Bilfa Nursery lines; 23 F8 Sugars-Drought lines; 16 F8 Sugars-Farmer Selection and 16 Drought lines-Ex-Malawi established on 16th June, 2007 and harvested on 22nd September, 2007 at Kasinthula Research Station. The aim was phenotypically screen these regional lines for drought tolerance. The experimental nursery units consisted of 1 row of 4 m long by 0.6 m wide with beans planted 0.10 m between plants. Irrigation water was applied at two levels: Non Water Stressed (NS) by maintaining the soil water storage at 70% and Drought Stressed (DS) by maintaining the soil water storage at 30% of its field capacity. Drought Intensity Index (DII), drought susceptibility index (DSI), half percentage reduction (PR) and geometrical means (GM) were determined on seed yield, pod yield and number of pods per plant to compare genotypes response to water and non-water stressed conditions. The results showed that drought stress effect on grain yield was moderate on F8 Sugars-Farmer selections, Ex-Columbia drought lines, Ex-Malawi, New Bilfa, and F8 Sugars-Drought lines as indicated by DH values of less than 0.2. Water stress resulted in yield reduction value of 19.6%, 15.4%, 18%, 21.4%, and 26.2% on Ex-Columbia, New Bilfa, F8 Sugars (Drought lines), F8 Sugars (Farmers selection) respectively. Ex-Columbia lines were more tolerant among the lines screened. It was therefore recommended that 14 lines out of 51 lines from Drought line-Ex-Columbia, 9 lines out of 26 from New Bilfa Nursery; 1 bean line out 23 lines from F8 Sugars (Drought Lines); 0 lines out 16 F8-Farmers selection and one line out of 16 lines for droughts lines-Ex-Malawi be advanced for further phenotypic screening for drought tolerance in dry season of 2008 basing on qualitative and quantitative analysis.
