TI  - Innovative activities for pro-poor development of Turkana pastoralists in Kenya.
T2  - Proceedings of the 12th International Conference of the Association of Institutions for Tropical Veterinary Medicine (AITVM), Montpellier, France, 20-22 August, 2007. Does control of animal infectious risks offer a new international perspective?
M3  - Book chapter
M3  - Conference paper
AB  - During the dry season 2005-2006 (October-March), drought conditions were particularly severe for the pastoral communities of Turkana Central and Southern Regions (North/West of Kenya). The majority of the population in these areas were forced to rely on relief food as they were faced severe food shortages as a result of the necessary migration of their animals to areas with adequate pasture and water. Some of the more severely affected families lost most of their livestock, meaning that they no longer had the capacity to rebuild their livelihoods once the drought was over.
