TI  - Grassroot participation and management for rural water-related envirommental problems in Ebo Itumbonuso, Ini Local Government Area, Akwa Ibom State, Nigeria.
T2  - International NGO Journal
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This article discusses grassroots' participation in providing sustainable and safe water for drinking, farming and other domestic and public uses in Ebo Itumbonuso, Ini Local Government Area, Akwa Ibom State, Nigeria. Women, youth and elders collaborate for the containment and abatement of the following water-related environmental problems: flooding, silting, pollution of water bodies; erosion; and outbreak of diseases. Suggested interventions centre on public awareness and education on and participation in waste minimization, reuse, recycling and management.
