TI  - Assessment of alternative maize trade and market policy interventions in Zambia.
T2  - Food security in Africa: market and trade policy for staple foods in Eastern and Southern Africa
M3  - Book chapter
AB  - This chapter examines the effects of historical policies on smallholder farm productivity and incomes, food price stability, and consumer food security in Zambia, and analyses possible alternative policy options and their anticipated impacts. The Chiluba government deregulated maize prices and private trade in the early 1990's but retained a little government role in the market and frequently arrange maize imports to ensure adequate food supplies during drought years. However, since 2005, the Mwanawasa government has substantially increased the role of the FRA. The government has tightened its control over the issuance of import and export permits.
