TI  - Spatial organization and adaptation strategy to drought of the nomads of the Arguin Bench National Park.
T2  - Secheresse
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This paper describes the spatial organization and adaptation strategy to drought of the nomads of the ARguin Bench National Park, Mauritania. It is established that the pastoralist population linked to the Park territory has adopted a strategy adapted to drought. This strategy is based on: (1) herd mobility; (2) zoning in small groups managed by shepherds and/or some members of the owner's family; (3) a range extension covering four regions (Adrar, Inchiri, Zemmour, Trarza); (4) feeding supplementation for animals; and (5) diversification of human activities: fishing and tourist camp management.
