TI  - Socio-economic status of fishers of two floodplain wetlands of West Bengal.
T2  - Environment and Ecology
M3  - Journal article
AB  - West Bengal in India is bestowed with a vast expanse of floodplain wetlands (beels). Evaluation of the socioeconomic milieu under which fishermen operate is a condition precedent to any worthwhile development strategy contemplated for the beels. Investigation carried out in Suguna beel under Suguna Fishers Cooperative Society and Amda beel under Dakshin Bishnupur Fishermen Cooperative Society reveals that the socioeconomic profile of the fishermen of Suguna beel is better than that of Amda beel, which is evident from the productions at 1527.16 kg/ha per year and 353.70 kg/ha per year, respectively. This was possible as the Suguna beel was a closed system and had been kept under better management.
