TI  - Municipal analysis of the incidence of hurricanes in mariculture regions of Mexico.
T2  - Veterinaria Mexico OA
M3  - Journal article
M3  - Conference paper
AB  - An analysis was conducted of the historical trajectory of hurricanes in Mexico (1974-2024), the temporal and spatial trends of continental trajectories, and their impact on the municipalities with the highest seafood production in Mexico. The results showed a higher incidence in two of the 20 municipalities with the highest aquaculture production, and in producing regions with low hurricane incidence (Sonora, Chiapas, and Baja California). Furthermore, an 11% annual increase in hurricane events was recorded, with no observed geographic shift. Hurricanes represent a relevant phenomenon in the adaptation of aquaculture production systems to climate change. This work is expected to contribute to aquaculture development planning in response to future global environmental changes.
