AU  - Bekele, A.
ED  - Dolan, C.
TI  - Oxfam's Somaliland-Ethiopia cross border drought preparedness project.
T2  - Field Exchange - Emergency Nutrition Network ENN
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This paper focuses on Oxfam UK's Somaliland-Ethiopia cross-border project. At the heart of the project is a concern to build strong, representative pastoral organizations, through which pastoralists can better understand and claim their rights and manage the development services they need. Principal aims include improved institutional capacity for drought preparedness linked to enhanced community preparedness capacity, and improved integrated natural resource management to ensure increased access to and availability of pasture, fodder and water so that households can preserve their assets. A key lesson from the early phases of the project is that the focus of pastoralist interventions should be to strengthen the community and risk reduction strategies, rather than simply fill material gaps through resource provision.
