TI  - Agricultural sci-tech information demand of farmer households and its influence factors in Qinba Mountainous Area, Chongqing.
T2  - Guizhou Agricultural Sciences
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The demand status of agricultural sic-tech information of farmer households is discussed by analyzing the investigation data from 1520 farmer households in 8 distracts (counties) of Qinba Mountainous Area in Chongqing. The factors to influence planting technique and good variety information demand of farmer households are analyzed by the established model to provide a reference for effective acquirement of agricultural sci-tech information of farmer households in impoverished mountainous area. Results: The agricultural sci-tech information demand of farmer households involves planting technique, breeding technique, good varieties, market supply and demand of agricultural products, agricultural policy, agro-technical training, agrometeorology, and disaster prediction and protection but the agricultural sci-tech information demand of farmer households focuses on planting and breeding technique mainly. There is difference in agricultural sci-tech information demand between farmer households with different feature but the general demand degree of farmer households is higher. The planting technique information demand of farmer households is affected by individual educational level, family scale and farming income. Information exchange, technological sharing, general income and production scale influence the good variety information demand of farmer households. The planting technique and good variety information demand of farmer households is affected by individual educational level, price of agricultural products, preferential policy and farming subsidy at the same time.
