TI  - Can one animal represent an entire herd? Modeling pastoral mobility using GPS/GIS technology.
T2  - Human Ecology
M3  - Journal article
AB  - GPS tracking devices on different animals in two separate herds were stationed in two different locations in the Logone Floodplain in the Far North of Cameroon. Analysis were done to examine whether one animal can represent the grazing behaviour of the entire herd in pastoral systems. Results showed that the daily movements result both from the herders' management as well as the social dynamics of the animals in the herd. It was also observed that despite the complexities of the interplay between herders' management and cattle's social behaviour tracking one animal with GPS is a valid method tostudy movements and grazing behaviour of an entire cattle herd in mobile pastoral systems.
