TI  - Climate change impact - a novel, initiative for Kerala.
T2  - Indian Journal of Geo-Marine Sciences
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This paper presents a study that aims to integrate climate change information into development and adaptation efforts. Specifically, the study explores the following topics: (1) trends in climatic elements, their spatial pattern and its relationship with extreme events such as El Nino, cyclones, etc.; (2) impact of climate change to the following sectors of Kerala, viz., agriculture (including plantation crops and spices), fisheries (marine and inland), industries, transport-vehicular and inland water transports, tourism, biodiversity, forestry, and road maintenance; and (3) spatial and temporal changes in water resources (quantity and quality of surface and groundwater). It is established that the study will lead to strategic interventions for developing capacity to improve governance in the coastal regions under various scenarios of climate change and extreme weather events.
