TI  - Natural Disaster, food insecurity and their impacts on social justice in gender perspective in Bangladesh.
T2  - South Asian Anthropologist
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Natural Disaster in terms of flood, draught, cyclone, storm, water stagnation and water salinity, landslide, arsenic contamination in ground water and river bank erosion are common phenomena and regular feature in Bangladesh. Every year lives, properties and crops are being destroyed by natural disasters. A large number of people are become vulnerable and they live in inhuman condition. The main objective of this paper is to examine to what extent the natural disasters affect social justice in relation to food security and nutrition, health and child care, housing and accommodation, disintegration of women and children from family tie, and education in gender perspective upon post disaster stage.
