TI  - ILRI's index-based livestock insurance: hope for Kenya's pastoralists.
T2  - Rural 21
M3  - Journal article
AB  - It is reported that the International Livestock Research Institute (ILRI), in collaboration with its technical partners, has developed an Index-Based Livestock Insurance, an innovative satellite based insurance that will compensate pastoralists in Kenya for livestock lost due to drought. In January 2010, ILRI, together with its commercial partners, UAP Insurance and Equity Insurance Agency, launched a pilot project in Marsabit District in northern Kenya, where nearly 2000 contracts were sold.
