TI  - Does clone matter to tea growers and buyers.
T2  - TRFK Quarterly Bulletin
M3  - Journal article
AB  - Over the years, the Tea Research Foundation of Kenya has released a total of 47 clones to the Kenyan tea. This paper discusses the adoption of clones in tea cultivation by smallholder and estate sectors in Kenya, and briefly describes the characteristics (including adaptability, yield performance and quality) of these clones in comparison to existing cultivars. An illustration is provided of 4 developed clonal tea cultivars (2 released and 2 promising clones) with the information to be contained in the proposed clonal catalogue that will be made available in the tea industry and to other interested parties. Data on their morphology, yield and quality potential, abiotic (such as drought) and biotic (pests and diseases) resistances are shown.
