T2  - Informe GEPEC
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The municipality of Dianopolis is located in the Southeast region of the State of Tocantins, and presents challenges in terms of local development, as it is in a region with prolonged droughts, a factor that interferes with its main economic activity, which is agriculture. This article aims to characterize the agricultural strategies adopted by bodies in the municipality of Dianopolis and the state of Tocantins to serve small rural producers in family farming. The methodology applied was based on an exploratory approach, with documentary analysis, field research, questionnaire application to local family farming producers and interviews with agricultural managers. It was identified that despite the economic representation of the agricultural sector in the municipality of Dianopolis/TO and the stimulus for the continuity of the activity, family farming encounters difficulties with the lack of technical assistance, and mainly, in relation to local public policies dedicated to meeting the needs of the sector.
