AU  - Sujatha, J. J.
AU  - Palaniswamy, A.
TI  - Gender variation in training needs and farming constraints in different farming systems.
T2  - Journal of Ecobiology
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The decisions of farmers and farm women are important for adoption of recommended package of practices. They should also develop and have good knowledge of different farming technologies. Enthusing them to acquire knowledge and skill on farm technologies through training will further enable them to take proper decisions on farm problems. The study focused on analysing the training needs of farmers and farm women in agriculture, animal husbandry, poultry, fodder crops, sericulture and mushroom cultivation. Besides the farming, constraints were also analysed. The data were gathered through personal interviews to 240 respondents from Coimbatore and Periyar districts, Tamil Nadu, India. Pest and disease management and inter-cultural operational practices were the training needs expressed by majority of the farmers and farm women in different farming systems. Pest problem, disease problem, water scarcity and lack of labour were the constraints expressed by the farmers and farm women.
