T2  - Documentos - Embrapa, Centro de Pesquisa Agropecuaria do Oeste
M3  - Bulletin
AB  - A proportional stratified sample (n=17 individuals) was taken to collect information about characteristics of fish farms, fish species, management practices, commercialization, and some technical coefficients. Average flooded surface of pond areas was 21.16 ha varying from 0.35 to 122.90 ha. In general, small fish farms had more water available for replacement and renewing, and thus, could use higher populational density, and had better productivity than others. Productivity average was estimated at 3082 kg/ha/year. The main species grown werePseudoplatystomasp.,Piaractus mesopotamicus, Ictalurus punctatus, Piaractus mesopotamicus*Colossoma macropomumandOreochromis niloticuscorresponding to 96.5% of the total production in 2004. Fish breeders used different commercialization techniques, mainly fish industry and fee-fishing. Most of them were pleased with the undertaking, and the annual mean income was 35%.
